17/06/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Authorities announced on Saturday (June 16th) the arrests of three senior officials at the Croatian Privatisation Fund for alleged corruption.
They are accused of various misappropriations, amounting to thousands of euros in losses to the state budget.
Chief Prosecutor Mladen Bajic says six people have been arrested and one more is being sought.
(Vecernji list - 17/06/07;
HRT, Index.hr - 16/06/07)
